-y=x^2-2x-7=(x-1)^2-8\implies (x-1)^2=-(y-8)
x-1=Y,y-8=X
Y^2=-X=2\left(-\frac12\right)X
y = -x^2 + 2x + 7 
y = -(x^2 - 2x +1)+8 
y = -(x- 1)^2+8 
(x- 1)^2=-(y-8) 
(x- 1)^2=2(-\frac{1}{2})(y-8)\Rightarrow p=-\frac{1}{2},x-1=Y,y-8=X 
Y^2=2pX
